cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for image super-resolution, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The method also involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and a feedback mechanism, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to handle complex tasks, which involves the use of curriculum learning, which is related to neural networks and optimization, and hence cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category.
